-- Buffett Adds to Wells Fargo Stake, Tells CNBC Bank is Well Run
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2012-10-24T11:18:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-24/buffett-adds-to-wells-fargo-stake-tells-cnbc-bank-is-well-run.html
Warren Buffett , the billionaire
chairman of Berkshire Hathaway Inc., has increased his stake in
 Wells Fargo & Co. (WFC)  in the past week, he told CNBC.  “Wells is very well run,” Buffett, 82, told the business
news station in an interview today without disclosing the size
of his latest purchases of the San Francisco-based bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
